simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is invoked during FM application startup initialization to create and initialize the FM file system free space table. The purpose for the table is to define the list of file systems for which free space must be reported.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is called from the CFE Table Services as part of the initial table load, and later inresponse to a Table Validate command. The function verifies that the table data is acceptable to populate the FM file system free space table.

parameterdescription.para: - Pointer to table data for verification.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is invoked to acquire a pointer to the FM file system free space table data. The pointer is maintained in the FM global data structure. Note that the table data pointer will be set to NULL if the table has not yet been successfully loaded.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is invoked to release the pointer to the FM file system free space table data. The pointer is maintained in the FM global data structure. The table data pointer must be periodically released to allow CFE Table Services an opportunity to load or dump the table without risk of interfering with users of the table data.
